							<h2>Loan against LIC Policy</h2>
							<p>Get flexibility of liquidity and access to cash when you need it, without selling off your LIC Policies.</p>
							<p>A life insurance policy is designed to provide financial cover to your family if something happens to you. Certain types of policies such as unit-linked and endowment plans also double up as investments. But now your insurance plan can also help you raise funds when you need it through a loan against insurance policy.</p>
							
							<h4>Features and Benefits</h4>
							<ul>
								<li>Get up to 80% of surrender value.</li>
								<li>Tenure - Loan tenure up to 12 months</li>
								<li>Easy Documentation</li>
								<li>Only pay interest</li>
							</ul>
							
							<h4>Eligibility</h4>
								<ul>
									<li>Resident individuals (Maharashtra state only)</li>
									<li>Should be a member of Mchurner</li>
									<li>Valid LIC Policy </li>
									<li>Income eligibility based on latest salary slip and Form 16</li>
									<li>Age 21 to 60</li>
								</ul>
							<p>The above criteria are subject to change from time to time at the sole discretion of Mchurner Nidhi Limited.</p>
							
							<h4>Documents required</h4>
							<ul>
								<li><strong>Proof of identity:</strong> Valid passport/Voter’s ID/Valid Driving license with photo graph /Pan card /Aadhar card</li>
								<li><strong>Proof of Income:</strong> Latest 3 months salary slip / certificate for fixed salary/Latest Form 16 and Last 6 months bank statement/Passbook of the salary account</li>
								<li><strong>Proof of residence:</strong> Latest Electricity Bill/utility bill/ piped gas bill/ telephone bill (Not more than 2 months old)/ Passport/Aadhar card/ Voter ID/ Driving  License.</li>
							</ul>
							
